# Security rules (AsFix & Gear)

## Secrets & env

- Never commit `.env`, `backend/data/data.json` tokens, or real admin passwords.
- Default admin password is seed-only; remind user to run `npm run reset-admin` after deploy.
- Use `process.env.ADMIN_PASSWORD` in seed scripts, not hardcoded production secrets.
- Run `node scripts/check-secrets.js` before merging sensitive changes.

## Auth

- Staff routes must use existing auth middleware in `backend/routes/` — do not bypass token checks.
- Frontend stores token in `localStorage` (`asfix_auth_token`); never log tokens or password hashes.
- Admin/staff UI is gated by `useAuth()` / `isStaff` — keep those checks on mutating actions.

## API safety

- Validate and sanitize user input on the backend (repairs, contact, orders, products).
- Keep JSON body limit reasonable (`express.json({ limit: '5mb' })`).
- Do not expose internal paths, stack traces, or raw `data.json` in API responses.

## Rate limiting & abuse

- Prefer server-side validation over client-only checks for forms (repair booking, contact, checkout).
- When adding public POST endpoints, consider basic rate limiting or duplicate-submission guards.

## Dependencies

- Avoid adding heavy auth libraries unless needed; match existing Express + JSON file store pattern.
